-- Edison, Monte Paschi, STMicro, UniCredit May Move: Italy Equity Preview
-- Francesca Angelini
-- 2010-07-23T06:52:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/bongrain-scor-alstom-bourbon-legrand-pernod-french-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in Paris. Stock
symbols are in parentheses after company names. Share prices are
from the last close.  
 France’s CAC 40 Index climbed 3.1 percent to 3,600.57 at
the close of trading in Paris. The broader SBF 120 Index rose
2.9 percent to 2,672.89.  
 Alstom SA  (ALO FP): The world’s third-largest power-
equipment maker won two contracts worth 450 million euros ($580
million) to design, build and maintain two combined cycle gas
units for GVK Industries in India. The shares added 2.8 percent
to 37.17 euros.  
 BioAlliance Pharma SA  (BIO FP): The pharmaceutical company
said second-quarter revenue jumped to a record 15.2 million
euros from 1.5 million euros a year earlier. The shares rose 3.6
percent to 5.48 euros.  
 Bongrain SA  (BH FP): The maker of Coeur de Lion camembert
cheese said first-half revenue rose to 1.66 billion euros from
1.58 billion euros a year earlier. The shares closed unchanged
at 56.51 euros.  
 Bourbon SA  (GBB FP): The owner of the second-biggest fleet
of supply and crew ships for the oil industry confirmed the sale
of 16 supramax carriers for $545 million to Genco Shipping &
Trading Ltd. The shares added 1.6 percent to 34.52 euros.  
 Inter Parfums SA  (ITP FP): The scent designer reported
first-half sales of 150.7 million euros and raised its forecast
for full-year revenue. The shares rose 2.3 percent to 24.20
euros.  
 Legrand SA  (LR FP): The French maker of electrical switches
and plugs made an offer to buy Indo Asian Fusegear Ltd.’s
switchgear division. The companies didn’t disclose financial
terms. The shares rose 4.8 percent to 25.22 euros.  
 Pernod Ricard SA  (RI FP): The maker of Absolut vodka and
Chivas Regal whiskey raised its full-year profit forecast for
the second time. Profit from recurring operations will rise 3
percent to 4 percent this year, up from a previous estimate of
growth of about 3 percent. Sales excluding revenue from
acquisitions advanced “close to 3 percent” in the fiscal
fourth quarter. The shares added 2 percent to 64.11 euros.  
 Scor SE  (SCR FP): The French reinsurer said property and
casualty and specialty treaty renewals at the end of June showed
premium growth of 19 percent, excluding currency fluctuations.
The shares closed unchanged at 15.61 euros.  
 Societe Television Francaise 1  (TFI FP): The owner of
France’s most-watched television channel said first-half profit
rose by 51 percent and increased its full-year revenue guidance
as advertising sales rose. The stock added 2 percent to 11.70
euros.  
